5/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2Fd3%2F0f81e92d415dbca7695a603f47e9%2Fimg-20180128-191144046.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4608x3456+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2Fd3%2F0f81e92d415dbca7695a603f47e9%2Fimg-20180128-191144046.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4608x3456+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2Fd3%2F0f81e92d415dbca7695a603f47e9%2Fimg-20180128-191144046.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4608x3456+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2Fd3%2F0f81e92d415dbca7695a603f47e9%2Fimg-20180128-191144046.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4608x3456+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2Fd3%2F0f81e92d415dbca7695a603f47e9%2Fimg-20180128-191144046.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4608x3456+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2Fd3%2F0f81e92d415dbca7695a603f47e9%2Fimg-20180128-191144046.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4608x3456+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2Fd3%2F0f81e92d415dbca7695a603f47e9%2Fimg-20180128-191144046.jpg" class="img" alt="Alison Wong and her family reconnect over a hot pot meal for the Lunar New Year." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Along with a sweet treat, Alison Wong and her family enjoy hot pot for the Lunar New Year.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Courtesy Alison Wong                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;"What you do on the first day of the new year is how your year will go," said Rebe C. of Annandale, Va., "On New Year's Day, I live as if it's my 'perfect day.' I wake up early, meditate, spend quality time with family, and dedicate time to the hobby I want to focus on throughout the year.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Thao Bui of New York City and her partner believe that the first person who walks into your home sets the tone for the entire year. That's why her partner takes a walk around the neighborhood on the New Year before returning home, as part of a Vietnamese custom known as &lt;em&gt;xông đất. &lt;/em&gt;"We don't want any zodiac signs clashing with ours to bring bad luck," she said.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Lucky color red&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-44565" class="bucketwrap image small"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2268;         --source-height: 4032;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/300/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 168px, (min-width: 1025px) 168px, (min-width: 768px) 252px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/300/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg 800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 168px, (min-width: 1025px) 168px, (min-width: 768px) 252px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2268x4032+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F37%2Fe7%2F6d25c6514913bce809132201cd5a%2Fdragon-decor.jpg" class="img" alt="Nguyen&amp;#039;s mother uses the lucky envelopes her daughter makes as Lunar New Year decor." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Stacy Nguyen's mother uses the lucky envelopes her daughter makes as Lunar New Year decor.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Courtesy Stacy Nguyen                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Just like Christmas and Halloween, decorations play a big part in Lunar New Year festivities. Athan Lau's family uses red decorations to sweep out bad luck from the past year. He also remembers watching red firecrackers as a kid every new year.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;"Red symbolizes happiness, luck, and celebration, all from the Legend of Nian," Lau said. "Nian was a folklore monster who ate people from a Chinese village until one day, an old man came and told the people to make loud noises, decorate their homes in red, and create bright light. Today, we dress and decorate in red and gold because it brings good fortune to our family. We also celebrate together to honor family values and our great-grandparents and ancestors who came before us."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Eat your way to good fortune&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Many foods eaten during the Lunar New Year symbolize good luck or prosperity.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Chelsea Tan, originally from Malaysia, and Steven Teo, originally from Singapore, participate in the "prosperity toss," also known as &lt;em&gt;yee sang &lt;/em&gt;or &lt;em&gt;lo hei. &lt;/em&gt;This tradition involves tossing a salad made with fish and other crunchy vegetables.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tan says the ingredients in the salad represent different things: fish for abundance, vegetables for vitality and so on. Participants gather around the table and toss the salad as high as possible while shouting things for good luck. "The higher you toss, the luckier you are," Tan said.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-44558" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5184;         --source-height: 3456;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG" class="img" alt="Chelsea Tan and her friends participate in a &amp;quot;prosperity toss&amp;quot; for the Lunar New Year." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Chelsea Tan and her friends participate in a "prosperity toss" for the Lunar New Year.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Courtesy Chelsea Tan                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Teo, who calls this dish &lt;em&gt;lo hei, &lt;/em&gt;says &lt;em&gt;lo &lt;/em&gt;means to mix but can also mean the act of doing business. "So tossing the salad higher means your business or work will improve next year. Hei means happiness."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mary Yee fondly remembers her mother and aunts making dumplings on the Lunar New Year as the family gathered for a large meal. Although my grandparents and parents are no longer with us, I am grateful for their sharing these traditions with me so that I may pass them along to my children, grandchildren, and the generations to come," she said.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Dress for success&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-44566" class="bucketwrap image medium"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3580;         --source-height: 5370;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/300/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 1600w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 300px, (min-width: 1025px) 300px, (min-width: 768px) 252px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/300/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 1600w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 300px, (min-width: 1025px) 300px, (min-width: 768px) 252px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" class="img" alt="Kristen Morita dresses her and her daughter up in traditional and modern Chinese cheongsam." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Kristen Morita dresses her and her daughter up in traditional and modern Chinese cheongsam.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Courtesty Kristin Morita                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Many readers look forward to wearing a new outfit to symbolize a fresh start. Others like to wear clothing that is traditional to their cultures, like food blogger Kristen Morita, who wears a traditional Chinese cheongsam for the holiday. She says she wore her mother's cheongsam to her wedding and later learned that more modern interpretations of the dress are available. Now, she and her children celebrate their traditions through fashion.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Lena Chen of Sebastopol, Calif., did not grow up with a lot of money. She remembers when her mother saved all year to buy fabrics to make new clothes for her as a child. "It was the most beautiful red dress my sister and I had ever worn! After all these years, I still remember it as a labor of love from my mother."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In addition to the clothes, some believe your hair can determine your luck for the year. Karen Yee of San Francisco, says she doesn't cut or wash her hair on New Year's Day. "Hair and luck in Chinese are homonyms," she said. "So if you cut or wash your hair on the day of the Lunar New Year, it means you are washing or cutting the luck you have at the start of the year."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-44569" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 640;         --source-height: 480;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+